WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.030 --> 00:00:03.230
Materials discovery can now imagine millions of crystals.

2
00:00:03.230 --> 00:00:06.030
Google DeepMind's GNoME proposed 2.2 million.

3
00:00:06.030 --> 00:00:10.030
But by late 2023, only 736 had been independently synthesized.

4
00:00:10.030 --> 00:00:12.830
The scarce resource is no longer prediction.

5
00:00:12.830 --> 00:00:14.030
It is trust.

6
00:00:14.030 --> 00:00:15.253
Every stage leaks.

7
00:00:15.253 --> 00:00:17.291
Generators omit complex material classes.

8
00:00:17.291 --> 00:00:21.775
Universal machine-learned potentials are least reliable at surfaces, vacancies, and defects.

9
00:00:21.775 --> 00:00:24.221
And laboratories inherit every upstream error.

10
00:00:24.221 --> 00:00:27.890
More activity does not automatically produce more validated materials.

11
00:00:27.890 --> 00:00:30.020
Lupine Science sits between prediction and synthesis.

12
00:00:30.020 --> 00:00:38.540
It measures a predictor's systematic error as a physical field over local atomic environments,
corrects that error at runtime, and proves which claims remain inside the evidence boundary.

13
00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:40.884
The field is fixed by three standard observables.

14
00:00:40.884 --> 00:00:43.814
A fourth surface is held back as a blind test.

15
00:00:43.814 --> 00:00:49.380
Across 36 model-and-material combinations, predicted and measured errors correlate
at zero point nine oh six, with zero adjustable parameters.

16
00:00:49.380 --> 00:00:53.021
Quantitative claims are then sealed as Lean 4 theorems with hash-locked provenance.

17
00:00:53.021 --> 00:00:56.358
The proof layer has 190 build-locked theorems and zero unfinished proofs.

18
00:00:56.358 --> 00:00:59.999
It once rejected a rounded success count, changing 27 improvements to 26.

19
00:00:59.999 --> 00:01:02.730
Trust means being able to say no to yourself.

20
00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:07.144
The correction deploys beside existing CHGNet
or MACE calculators as a LAMMPS overlay.

21
00:01:07.144 --> 00:01:09.861
In Python, measured overhead is 15.6 percent.

22
00:01:09.861 --> 00:01:15.294
On a blind nickel surface, relative error
fell from 9.7 percent to 1.5 percent.

23
00:01:15.294 --> 00:01:16.652
Users keep their simulators.

24
00:01:16.652 --> 00:01:18.350
Lupine makes them more trustworthy.

25
00:01:18.350 --> 00:01:24.818
Better materials infrastructure is estimated to create 123 to
270 billion dollars in annual value for United States industry.

26
00:01:24.818 --> 00:01:28.903
Against that scale, Lupine's 36-month budget is about 3.2 million dollars.

27
00:01:28.903 --> 00:01:31.967
The investment is not a bet on one material.

28
00:01:31.967 --> 00:01:34.350
It is leverage across every screened material.

29
00:01:34.350 --> 00:01:36.076
The face-centered-cubic field is established.

30
00:01:36.076 --> 00:01:40.565
Other structure families and industrial validation
remain open work, with explicit go-or-no-go gates.

31
00:01:40.565 --> 00:01:42.291
That honesty is the product.

32
00:01:42.291 --> 00:01:45.053
The world does not need more predicted crystals.

33
00:01:45.053 --> 00:01:47.470
It needs predictions laboratories can act on.
